content.detailedDescription:
I was fishing in an outlet off of white river, near knob hill, arkansas. i was with three other people, yet i was the only one that saw this thing. i noticed this object because of the bright glow. it was teardrop shape, the large end being the "head of it" and it was below tree top level, luminescent everywhere and it made absolutely no noise. it was following the river and it came from behind some trees, passed through a clearing because it was over water, and simply disappeared behind more trees. i grabbed my step-brother's arm immediately. and asked him, "did you see that"? he didn't. my other step-brother and his girlfriend did not see it either but i got hysterical. i knew what it was. no doubt in my mind. i was 14 at the time. and they did not believe me, period. i don't care, i know what i saw. (i even used this event as one of my speech presentations.) i jumped up after seeing it and begged them to take me in the car to follow it and they wouldn't. so, that was it. but i have never forgotten the details, and i never will. i can draw a picture of it to this day and now i am 48. it's been 34 years. and it was not swamp gas. swamp gas doesn't fly by sideways, (or so i would presume), and we were on a river, not near any kind of swamp.

{pid}
may 25, 2009
